  <amendments/>
  <summary>7/25/2006--Introduced.
Calls for: (1) cessation of the targeting by any side in the hostilities in Lebanon of infrastructure vital to non-combatants, which also increases the likelihood of the loss of innocent civilian life; (2) immediate opening of a secure humanitarian corridor via the seaports and airports of Lebanon to alleviate the suffering of the people of Lebanon; and (3) an immediate cease-fire. Urges a comprehensive and just solution to the Arab-Israeli conflict.</summary>
